Purpose: Degree awarded for the successful completion of this, academic program.  This will be the degree assigned, to any student enrolled in this program.  This is not, kept on the student's record, so once a student has, been assigned to this academic program, the student, will receive whatever degree is attached to the, academic program when the student completes the, requirements.
This is the number of months in a typical term for this, program.  It is used as a default to FPST.TERM.LENGTH, where it can be changed as needed.
The academic level associated with this program.  This, is the academic level that will be used for any, student in this program.  It defaults from the, department academic level, but can be changed.

Default Input Processing: XL.IDS = "", CALL S.GET.REGION.LOCATIONS(XL.IDS,EDITED.DATA), IF XL.IDS THEN, $BUILD.LOOKUP.FLAG.LIST, END ELSE,    VALIDATION OFF,    LOOKUP NO_ADD, END
Purpose: Locations at which this program is offered.  If, entered, then one of the locations must be assigned, to the students in the program.  Not otherwise used, by the system.

Says whether or not this academic program can be, used by a person in evaluating an academic program, change.  Some academic programs may be set up as, templates or basic requirements, but not one is, to actually enroll in those.  For that type of, academic program, this field would be No., Regular programs that should be usable by, students would have this field set to Yes.
The grade scheme associated with this academic, program.  It is used to default to the academic, requirements for this program whenever minimum, grades are specified.
Description of the invoice item.  Defaults from AR, code description, but can be changed.  Displays on, item lists and resolution screens.
Envision-maintained login of who added this record.
